# Digital Signal Processing: Mathematics to Intelligent Signal Processing
[![LaTeX](https://img.shields.io/badge/LaTeX-Book-green)]()
[![Elsevier Template](https://img.shields.io/badge/Elsevier-Book-blue)]()
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-TBD-lightgrey)]()

## Overview

This repository contains the complete source code for the book **Digital Signal Processing: Mathematics to Intelligent Signal Processing**.

The manuscript is written in LaTeX using the Elsevier Book Template and provides a comprehensive treatment of digital signal processing, spanning classical signal processing theory, modern optimization methods, adaptive filtering, multidimensional signal processing, and data-driven intelligent signal processing.

---

## Book Structure

The manuscript currently consists of **22 technical chapters**.

### Chapters

1. Packages, Libraries and Language
2. Sampling and Quantization
3. Basic Digital Modulation
4. Digital PID Controllers
5. Convolution and LTI Systems
6. The Discrete Fourier Transform (DFT)
7. The Fast Fourier Transform (FFT) and Windowing
8. The Z-Transform and System Functions
9. Finite Impulse Response (FIR) Filters
10. Multirate DSP (Decimation and Interpolation)
11. Advanced Multi-Rate and Filter Bank Theory
12. Adaptive Filtering
13. IQ Modulation and Software Defined Radio (SDR)
14. Random Signals and Power Spectral Density (PSD)
15. Stochastic Digital Signal Processing
16. Fixed-Point DSP and Hardware Consideration
17. The Phase-Locked Loop (PLL) Synchronization Engine
18. Finite Word-Length Stability Analysis
19. Two-Dimensional Spatial Frequency and Image Compression
20. Advanced Multidimensional and Array Processing
21. Sparsity and Optimization-Driven DSP
22. Data-Driven and Intelligent Signal Processing

Additional material includes:

- Preface
- Appendix
- References
- Glossary
- About the Author(s)

---

## Repository Layout

```
book/
│
├── book.tex                 # Master compilation file
├── main.tex                 # Main manuscript
├── titlepage.tex
├── preface.tex
├── tableofcontents.tex
├── chapter*.tex
├── appendix*.tex
├── references.bib
├── references.tex
├── contributors.tex
├── aboutauthors.tex
├── glossary.tex
├── listoffigures.tex
└── README.md
```

---

## Compilation

Compile using

```
pdflatex
bibtex
pdflatex
pdflatex
```

or simply compile using Overleaf.

---

## Bibliography

The bibliography is maintained in

```
references.bib
```

A manually formatted bibliography can also be generated using

```
references.tex
```

